parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brake caliper can cause the brakes to lock up, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The rear brake caliper locks up
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brakes are slow to release
the vehicle drags to a stop even when no pressure is being applied
fire in the rear underchassis.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS and brake lights are on
the brakes are slow to release
the vehicle drags to a stop even when no pressure is being applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Axle and Wheel Bearing Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front axle and wheel bearings can cause the wheel to come off while driving, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The wheel comes off while driving
often without warning
and may be accompanied by unusual noises or vibrations. In some cases
the wheel bearing may give warning signs before failure
such as noise
vibration
or play in the wheel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of the front wheel bearing can cause the wheel to separate from the vehicle, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The wheel bearing breaks off without warning
the wheel and tire fly off the vehicle
the vehicle may vibrate or pull to one side
loss of control or difficulty steering.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Insufficient Wheel Bearing Design or Manufacturing
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wheel bearing can be attributed to a design or manufacturing defect, which can lead to premature failure, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The wheel bearing breaks off without warning
the wheel and tire fly off the vehicle
the vehicle may vibrate or pull to one side
loss of control or difficulty steering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front crankshaft oil seal can cause significant oil leaks, leading to engine damage, increased risk of engine failure, and potential safety hazards due to reduced visibility on the road.
symptoms: Oil leaks from the front of the engine
oil spots under the vehicle
increased oil consumption
engine noise or vibration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden rupture of the fuel line assembly can cause diesel fuel to spray onto the vehicle and highway, posing a significant fire hazard and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Fuel leakage
fuel spraying onto the vehicle and highway
fractured fuel lines
fuel line assembly failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the recall repair to properly address the fuel system issue can lead to continued fuel line assembly failures, posing a risk to vehicle safety and occupants.
symptoms: Fuel leakage
fuel spraying onto the vehicle and highway
fractured fuel lines
fuel line assembly failure
inadequate recall repair.
